<h2 class="nounderline">Become a Volunteer</h2>


<!--BEGIN CONTENT-->

<p>
Volunteers play an important part in the success of PACER Center. Have a few 
spare hours? Help at events, be a puppeteer, prepare mailings, or offer your 
other unique talents to PACER.</p>
<ul class="nobullet">
	<li>
		<strong><a href="/help/events.asp">Special Events</a></strong><br />
		PACER holds a variety of community events throughout the year, and needs volunteers to participate on planning committees and to help with set-up and registration at the events. Previous events have included the HOT Party, Annual Benefit, and Family Fun Day.<br /><br />
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong><a href="/funtimes/">Fun Times</a></strong><br />
		Fun Times is a volunteer social program that connects high school teens with and without disabilities for various social outings and weekend activities. 
		PACER needs adult volunteers to assist with activities and collect paperwork. <br /><br />
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong><a href="/puppets/volunteer.asp">Be a Puppeteer with PACER</a></strong><br />
		Help PACER bring its puppet programs to area school children. The PACER puppets present informative, and entertaining programs in a child-friendly format. Please 
		fill out a <a href="/puppets/pdf/VolunteerApplication.pdf" target="_blank">Puppeteer application </a> <img border="0" src="/images/pdficon_small.gif" width="15" height="15" alt="pdf icon" /> and join us in this rewarding volunteer opportunity today!<br /><br />
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong><a href="/stc/">Simon Technology Center</a></strong><br />
		The Simon Technology Center needs volunteers to assist with its lending library, 
		open houses, workshops, and events.
	</li>
	<li>
		<br />
		<strong>Special Projects</strong><br />
		PACER Center needs volunteers for special projects throughout the year such as assisting in the front office or helping with the phonathon.
	</li>
</ul>

